  {% include "partials/nav.html.j2" %}

  <div class="jumbotron jumbo-white">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <span class="header"><h1><i>Crunchy Pasta with Chicken, Ricotta, Broccoli, and Lemon</i></h1></span>
      <div class="space"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <div class="header"><h3>INGREDIENTS</h3></div>
      <ul>
        <li><p>1/2 box of pasta (preferably a big tubular shape)</p></li>
        <li><p>1/2 lb chicken tenderloins (or "stir-fry" chicken)</p></li>
        <li><p>Broccoli</p></li>
        <li><p>1 big lemon (or 2 small lemons)</p></li>
        <li><p>Crushed red pepper flakes</p></li>
        <li><p>Salt</p></li>
        <li><p>Black pepper</p></li>
        <li><p>Cumin seeds</p></li>
        <li><p>Olive oil</p></li>
        <li><p>1/3 cup of unseasoned Panko bread crumbs</p></li>
        <li><p>1/3 grated parmesan</p></li>
        <li><p>Whole milk Ricotta</p></li>
        <p>Pro Tip&trade;: Make sure it is good Ricotta. If it has more than three ingredients, ditch it&mdash;it won't melt properly</p>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6">
      <div class="header"><h3>INSTRUCTIONS</h3></div>
      <ol>
        <li><p>Preheat the oven to 400.</p></li>
        <li><p>Quarter each chicken tenderloin. If you went with the "stir-fry" chicken, skip this step.</p></li>
        <li><p>Heat ~0.5 cm of oil in a skillet. When the oil is hot, add the chicken and season with salt and pepper.</p></li>
        <p>Pro Tip&trade;: Do not drop the chicken into the oil&mdash;it will splash on you&mdash; and don't burn your hands from leaping boiling oil droplets. Good luck.</p>
        <li><p>As the chicken is frying, begin boiling water for the pasta.</p></li>
        <li><p>Toss the broccoli in a bowl with olive oil, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper, and not-too-many cumin seeds.</p></li>
        <li><p>Spread the broccoli on a baking sheet. Cover the sheet with tinfoil beforehand if you don't want to wash it after this.</p></li>
        <li><p>Bake for about 20 minutes until soft and the edges are just starting to turn brown.</p></li>
        <li><p>Flip the chicken about halfway so it cooks evenly. It should be golden-brown on each side.</p></li>
        <li><p>Flip the broccoli after 10 minutes or so.</p></li>
        <li><p>Don't forget about the pasta.</p></li>
        <li><p>Begin zesting your lemon(s) as finely as possible. You'll want a tablespoon of zest.</p></li>
        <p>Pro Tip&trade;: use a microplane grater, it will be easier to clean.</p>
        <li><p>Mix 1/3 cup of parmesan, 1/3 cup Panko bread crumbs, a little salt and pepper, and your zest.</p></li>
        <p>Pro Tip&trade;: Don't spill the magic mixture all over the kitchen, it's a real pain.</p>
        <li><p>When the broccoli is done, switch the oven to broil.</p></li>
        <li><p>When the chicken is done, place it on a soft bed of paper towels to soak up any excess oil. You have cooked it too long when the oil starts smoking.</p></li>
        <li><p>Add the chicken and pasta to the baking sheet with their broccoli friends.</p></li>
        <li><p>Dollop with Ricotta. You like Ricotta.</p></li>
        <li><p>Spinkle your magic breadcrumb mixture on top.</p></li>
        <li><p>Give it a hearty drizzle of olive oil.</p></li>
        <li><p>Broil for a couple minutes to perfection.</p></li>
        <p>Pro Tip&trade;: You've come so far! Don't fuck it up now! Don't overbroil!</p>
        <li><p>Serve with a good squeeze of lemon.</p></li>
        <li><p>Enjoy a delicious meal. I'm happy for you.</p></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
